{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"promptId":"dcbe4efb-6e32-4db6-a75a-aa49b911d737","agentId":"a68890b8706007304","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"Research the fundamental \"verifier requirement\" and \"you can't bootstrap above your verifier / base capability\" limit in self-improving AI code systems, plus reward hacking / objective gaming. Use WebSearch and WebFetch tools (available to you).\n\nI need specific, cited claims about:\n1. The consensus that every working self-improver needs a GROUND-TRUTH EVALUATOR (unit tests, a benchmark, a formal verifier, a compiler) to provide the selection/training signal — without it the loop has no gradient and collapses. Find statements from AlphaEvolve, Darwin Godel Machine, STOP, and commentary/analysis articles articulating this.\n\n2. The \"generation-verification gap\" / \"verification is easier than generation\" idea (e.g. Leopold Aschenbrenner, or others) and how RSI depends on cheap verification. Also the related claim that a system cannot reliably produce code/solutions BETTER than what its verifier can validate, nor much beyond what its base model can already do — the loop amplifies/searches but does not exceed the verifier's discriminative power or the base model's latent capability. Find sources/analysis discussing this ceiling. Search terms: \"self-improvement requires verifier\", \"can't bootstrap above verifier\", \"verifier ceiling RSI\", \"generation verification gap LLM\".\n\n3. REWARD HACKING / specification gaming in self-improving loops: concrete documented examples where a self-improving/evolutionary code system gamed its objective rather than genuinely improving — e.g. editing the test/benchmark, faking results, special-casing test inputs, exploiting the evaluator. Include the Darwin Godel Machine objective-hacking observation, AlphaEvolve/evolutionary \"cheating\" the eval, and the general specification-gaming literature (DeepMind specification gaming, Goodhart's law applied to RSI). Cite.\n\n4. The role of base model capability: claims that RSI results so far are bounded by frontier model quality — the self-improvement is mostly better SCAFFOLDING/search on top of a fixed strong base model, not the model transcending itself. Cite.\n\nProvide exact source URLs for every claim. Return a structured list of falsifiable claims each with its URL."},"uuid":"263cabbf-cd72-43de-bcab-b4a368e9db0e","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:34:33.685Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
